<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0469</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Strong Thunderstorms Cut Through Central, Southern Plains</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Intense thunderstorms swept through the central and southern
Plains today with heavy rain, hail as big as golf balls and winds
that destroyed a boat dock and downed power lines.
   In north-central Texas near the Oklahoma border, the overnight
storms pelted View with golf ball-size hail and Burkburnett with
1-inch hail.
   Winds ripped down a carport, destroyed the boat dock and downed
electrical lines near Graham. Winds gusting to 60 mph in Olney
toppled trees.
   A line of thunderstorms brought high winds, hail and drenching
rains to western Missouri. Kansas City was deluged with 4 inches of
rain. A few people were trapped in cars after attempting to drive
through high water that pooled in low-lying areas. Near the
downtown airport, water 5 to 6 feet deep was reported.
   A strong thunderstorm near Maple City, Kan., brought hail the
size of golf balls.
   Showers and thunderstorms were also scattered over southeast
Georgia, Iowa, Mississippi and Alabama. Scattered showers fell over
eastern Colorado, Nebraska and South Dakota.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
over the Mississippi Valley and eastern portions of the Plains;
numerous showers and thunderstorms over the middle Mississippi
Valley; scattered showers and thunderstorms over the southern third
of Florida; strong, gusty winds over the northern Rockies; and
mostly sunny skies over the rest of the country.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 50s and 60s over the
middle and northern Atlantic Coast states, the Great Lakes, the
upper Mississippi Valley, Iowa, the central and northern Plains,
Oklahoma, and the central Rockies; in the 90s over south central
Texas, the desert Southwest and inland valleys of California; and
in the 70s and 80s through the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 29
degrees at Yellowstone National Park, Wyo., to 85 degrees at Yuma,
Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 65 partly cloudy; Boston 46 fair; Buffalo 44
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 70 fair; Cincinnati 60 fair; Cleveland 54
partly cloudy; Detroit 52 partly cloudy; Miami 76 fair; New York 53
fair; Philadelphia 56 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 53 fair; Portland,
Maine, 46 fair; Washington 60 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 46 cloudy; Chicago 57 foggy; Dallas-Fort
Worth 69 thunderstorms; Denver 40 fair; Des Moines 64 cloudy;
Indianapolis 60 partly cloudy; Kansas City 65 cloudy;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 52 foggy; Nashville 68 partly cloudy; New
Orleans 74 foggy; St. Louis 67 foggy.
   _West: Albuquerque 52 windy; Anchorage 34 fair; Las Vegas 72
fair; Los Angeles 63 fair; Phoenix 78 fair; Salt Lake City 45 fair;
San Diego 64 foggy; San Francisco 55 fair; Seattle 53 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 36 fair; Toronto 46 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
