<HEAD>Dukakis Has Flat Tire on Jersey Turnpike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ELIZABETH, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democratic presidential nominee Michael
Dukakis suffered a motorist's nightmare today, a flat tire on the
busy New Jersey Turnpike.
   But, unlike most motorists, when the right front tire of his
limousine went flat Dukakis had a backup car to move into.
   The presidential nominee was traveling in a motorcade from New
York, where he spent the night, to New Brunswick to deliver an
environmental speech at Rutgers University.
   No one was injured and the limo was left at the side of the
turnpike.
</TEXT>
