<DATELINE>CANBERRA, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Duchess of York decided Thursday
to extend her tour of Australia by two weeks to celebrate her
birthday with husband Prince Andrew, the Duke of York.
   That will increase the time that the duchess is spending away
from her newborn daughter, Beatrice, who stayed in London.
   ``Beatrice is not old enough yet to miss her mother. It's more
important I spend time with Andrew,'' the Daily Mail quoted her as
telling guests at an official dinner.
   The royal couple had been separated since shortly after
Beatrice's birth in early August when the duke left on a Far East
tour aboard HMS Edinburgh.
   The duke and duchess originally were to leave Australia on Oct.
7.
   The princess turns 29 on Oct. 18. The newspaper said the couple
is expected to leave the following day, the duchess by plane and
the duke aboard the ship, arriving home Dec. 16.
