<1ST_LINE>u a AM-Shuttle-GoodNight     09-29 0136</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Shuttle-Good Night,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>It's Been ``A Fun Day''</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPACE CENTER, Houston (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mission Control said good night to
the Discovery astronauts a little early on their first day in space.
   Their scheduled bedtime was not until 9:37 p.m. EDT, but at
8:15, Lacy Veach, the astronaut who works with the crew from
Mission Control, initiated this exchange:
   ``So we're going to say good night and not plan on talking to
you again. We certainly had a fun day working with you.''
   Discovery pilot Richard Covey responded: ``Well, Lacy we've had
a fun day too so far. We appreciate you all allowing us to settle
down here. We look forward to working with you all again tomorrow.''
   Veach: ``Roger that, same here. Good night from all of us.''
   Covey: ``Good night from America's spacecraft Discovery.''
</TEXT>
